299
00:18:23,300 --> 00:18:24,900
Xiaochun.

300
00:18:25,620 --> 00:18:27,200
Mr. Hu.

301
00:18:28,100 --> 00:18:30,580
I need to tell you something.

302
00:18:30,580 --> 00:18:34,340
Don't scold me because you think I'm meddlesome.

303
00:18:34,340 --> 00:18:37,599
I noticed that Xiao Hu Lu's grandparents came.

304
00:18:37,599 --> 00:18:40,060
So, I think I have to tell you this.

305
00:18:40,060 --> 00:18:43,000
Speak your mind.

306
00:18:44,260 --> 00:18:47,460
It's about Xiao Hu Lu's education.

307
00:18:49,140 --> 00:18:52,419
I know very little about education and I'm not a real teacher,

308
00:18:52,419 --> 00:18:55,159
but I need to get this off my mind by telling you.

309
00:18:55,159 --> 00:18:56,419
So, I insist on telling you.

310
00:18:56,420 --> 00:18:59,999
Can you please stop this nonsense? Cut to the chase.

311
00:19:03,860 --> 00:19:05,680
Haven't you noticed?

312
00:19:05,680 --> 00:19:08,600
Xiao Hu Lu has been feeling down today.

313
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:10,959
I did, but it's because she isn't standing in the middle.

314
00:19:10,959 --> 00:19:12,499
Kids just want to shine. I get it.

315
00:19:12,500 --> 00:19:13,960
Look at you!

316
00:19:13,960 --> 00:19:16,140
That's just the typical mindset of adults.

317
00:19:16,140 --> 00:19:18,240
What is Xiao Hu Lu thinking?

318
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:20,659
She thinks the middle is the best.

319
00:19:20,660 --> 00:19:23,779
If she can't be the best, her grandparents will complain

320
00:19:23,780 --> 00:19:26,740
the school here is bad and you can't educate her well.

321
00:19:26,740 --> 00:19:29,780
She can't study here anymore.

322
00:19:29,780 --> 00:19:33,820
She doesn't just want to be better than others.

323
00:19:33,820 --> 00:19:36,500
She's just scared of parting from you.

324
00:19:53,540 --> 00:19:56,160
Xiao Hu Lu, have some vegetables.

325
00:19:56,160 --> 00:19:57,579
Make sure you have balanced nutrition.

326
00:19:57,580 --> 00:19:59,019
Thank you, Grandpa.

327
00:19:59,020 --> 00:19:59,940
Good girl.

328
00:20:03,260 --> 00:20:05,400
Who said you're a fussy eater?

329
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:07,500
You aren't picky at all.

330
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:10,899
Grandma, my mom cooks yummy food for me every day.

331
00:20:10,899 --> 00:20:13,859
She even reads me stories and teaches me to read.

332
00:20:13,860 --> 00:20:16,480
Really? How many words do you know?

333
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:18,140
So many!

334
00:20:18,140 --> 00:20:23,580
I didn't stand in the middle today because I'm too tall.

335
00:20:23,580 --> 00:20:25,780
Having someone tall in the middle is quite disruptive.

336
00:20:25,780 --> 00:20:27,020
Yes!

337
00:20:27,020 --> 00:20:30,679
When you study in Kunming, Grandma will cook yummy food every day.

338
00:20:30,679 --> 00:20:33,260
I'll read you stories, too.

339
00:20:36,720 --> 00:20:40,460
Dad, I can agree with you on other things

340
00:20:40,460 --> 00:20:44,039
except for Xiao Hu Lu's education. We should discuss this again.

341
00:20:44,039 --> 00:20:45,719
This can't be negotiated.

342
00:20:45,719 --> 00:20:48,140
She must study in Kunming.

343
00:20:48,140 --> 00:20:50,179
We can't impede her education.

344
00:20:50,179 --> 00:20:52,480
We can't go with your decision on this.

345
00:20:52,980 --> 00:20:55,140
Here's my plan.

346
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:59,979
She can study elementary school here and attend junior high in Kunming.

347
00:20:59,979 --> 00:21:01,840
Won't she fall behind others?

348
00:21:01,840 --> 00:21:05,100
Others already have a good head start.

349
00:21:05,100 --> 00:21:07,620
If you insist on talking about head start,

350
00:21:07,620 --> 00:21:12,360
I reckon parents are the starting line for their children.

351
00:21:12,360 --> 00:21:17,139
After graduation, I started a small business and Luo Quan sold water purifiers.

352
00:21:17,139 --> 00:21:20,240
We could only provide her with very little.

353
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:24,659
So, I think the best thing we can offer her right now

354
00:21:24,660 --> 00:21:27,440
is a happy childhood and an unconstrained future.

355
00:21:27,440 --> 00:21:29,620
What are you even saying?

356
00:21:29,620 --> 00:21:31,380
Unconstrained?

357
00:21:31,380 --> 00:21:36,459
Xiao Hu Lu is so smart. She's bound to surpass both of you.

358
00:21:36,459 --> 00:21:40,080
Are you giving up on your child because you're incapable?

359
00:21:40,080 --> 00:21:42,060
How aren't I nurturing her?

360
00:21:42,060 --> 00:21:43,680
I've already sent her to school.

361
00:21:43,680 --> 00:21:45,500
What else do you want?

362
00:21:45,500 --> 00:21:47,490
Must she attend extra classes to learn instruments and painting?

363
00:21:47,499 --> 00:21:49,699
Must she study hard enough to win the Math Olympiad? Is this your concept of nurturing a child?

364
00:21:49,699 --> 00:21:51,920
Everyone lets their kids pick up the arts.

365
00:21:51,920 --> 00:21:55,240
She can. Our village is so cultured and artistic.

366
00:21:55,240 --> 00:21:58,439
I can let her learn embroidery, tie-dye, or carving.

367
00:21:58,439 --> 00:22:00,119
Recently, two painters visited our village.

368
00:22:00,119 --> 00:22:03,160
If necessary, I can introduce Xiao Hu Lu to them.

369
00:22:03,160 --> 00:22:05,479
Lower your voice. We're outside.

370
00:22:05,479 --> 00:22:06,740
Don't disturb others.

371
00:22:06,740 --> 00:22:08,560
That's right.

372
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:17,380
Xiaochun, what did we agree on?

373
00:22:17,960 --> 00:22:19,420
Yes, I remember.

374
00:22:19,420 --> 00:22:21,079
We did make a collective decision.

375
00:22:21,079 --> 00:22:23,800
However, we have to change according to her.

376
00:22:23,800 --> 00:22:27,680
She'll be useless if she grows up with you!

377
00:22:29,160 --> 00:22:30,840
What do you mean by that?

378
00:22:30,840 --> 00:22:33,100
She has a great habit of reading

379
00:22:33,100 --> 00:22:34,280
and a strong thirst for knowledge.

380
00:22:34,280 --> 00:22:38,820
She's brave, kind, caring, loyal, and polite.

381
00:22:38,820 --> 00:22:41,920
Do you know what her biggest dream is?

382
00:22:43,400 --> 00:22:45,640
She wants to be an astronaut.

383
00:22:45,640 --> 00:22:48,380
Is that being useless to you?

384
00:22:50,640 --> 00:22:51,860
Don't quarrel outside.

385
00:22:51,860 --> 00:22:53,940
Are you really a dad?

386
00:22:58,840 --> 00:23:02,200
There's no point of having you around. Fence-sitter.

387
00:23:02,200 --> 00:23:05,620
Stop eating. Let's go home.

388
00:23:05,620 --> 00:23:07,779
Enjoy the meal, Mom. Call me if necessary.

389
00:23:07,779 --> 00:23:09,200
Come on. Take your spoon.

390
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:10,860
The spoon!

391
00:23:11,520 --> 00:23:13,360
Xiaochun.

392
00:23:15,540 --> 00:23:18,460
I told you that you can't win her in a quarrel.

393
00:23:18,460 --> 00:23:20,719
We weren't quarreling. I was just stating facts.

394
00:23:20,719 --> 00:23:22,959
Dad, Xiaochun was also stating facts.

395
00:23:22,959 --> 00:23:24,920
Shut up.

396
00:23:24,920 --> 00:23:27,960
She's right. You're so useless.

397
00:23:27,960 --> 00:23:29,900
Just a fence-sitter.

398
00:23:38,160 --> 00:23:40,120
Mom, do you want some?

399
00:23:40,120 --> 00:23:42,620
No, thanks. Enjoy it yourself.

400
00:23:46,360 --> 00:23:49,860
Hu Lu, I want to ask you something.

401
00:23:49,860 --> 00:23:53,500
- Am I fierce?
- Yeah.

402
00:23:53,500 --> 00:23:55,460
Really?

403
00:23:58,880 --> 00:24:01,480
What do you hope for me to be like?

404
00:24:01,480 --> 00:24:04,080
Tell me and I'll change.

405
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:07,300
I want you to be happy.

406
00:24:08,280 --> 00:24:10,220
What else?

407
00:24:13,240 --> 00:24:18,299
Nothing else. You'll get full marks once you're happy.

408
00:24:25,900 --> 00:24:28,580
Hu Lu, let me tell you something.

409
00:24:28,580 --> 00:24:34,020
From now on, you don't have to excel at everything

410
00:24:34,020 --> 00:24:36,260
or win first place.

411
00:24:36,260 --> 00:24:39,860
You don't... have to be that sensible

412
00:24:39,860 --> 00:24:42,320
or try to please others.

413
00:24:42,320 --> 00:24:46,059
As long as you're happy, you don't have to excel at everything

414
00:24:46,059 --> 00:24:49,580
Really? I want to go shrimping at the riverside.

415
00:24:49,580 --> 00:24:51,140
No way.

416
00:24:52,640 --> 00:24:56,059
If I play at the riverside, you'll still beat me.

417
00:24:56,060 --> 00:24:57,740
Bingo.

418
00:25:05,800 --> 00:25:08,120
Hello, sir.

419
00:25:08,120 --> 00:25:10,660
Yes, I'm at Erhai North Road.

420
00:25:10,660 --> 00:25:12,520
I see.

421
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:15,360
Take your bag. Let's go.

422
00:25:15,880 --> 00:25:17,860
Get your water bottle.

423
00:25:29,560 --> 00:25:32,540
You're here. Give me a moment.

424
00:25:32,540 --> 00:25:34,180
They want to take some photos.

425
00:25:34,180 --> 00:25:35,820
Take photos?

426
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:39,460
A'Yao says they're for publicity.

427
00:25:41,160 --> 00:25:43,260
Is this Cang Mountain and Erhai Lake?

428
00:25:43,260 --> 00:25:46,100
Yes, it's a painting of these places.

429
00:25:46,100 --> 00:25:48,500
How long will it take to finish the embroidery?

430
00:25:48,500 --> 00:25:50,340
About several months.

431
00:25:50,340 --> 00:25:52,100
Look at me.

432
00:25:57,000 --> 00:25:59,000
What are you doing?

433
00:26:01,580 --> 00:26:03,420
Chairman Xie, I'm done.

434
00:26:03,420 --> 00:26:05,760
- I see.
- Okay.

435
00:26:08,720 --> 00:26:11,300
Ms. Xie, what do you want to give me?

436
00:26:11,300 --> 00:26:13,540
Just a piece of clothing.

437
00:26:18,060 --> 00:26:19,700
A traditional piece of clothing.

438
00:26:19,700 --> 00:26:21,980
These aren't common anymore.

439
00:26:21,980 --> 00:26:23,540
Look.

440
00:26:25,100 --> 00:26:27,480
It's gorgeous.

441
00:26:28,880 --> 00:26:31,680
This was my mom's dowry.

442
00:26:31,680 --> 00:26:35,180
My granny embroidered it.

443
00:26:42,760 --> 00:26:46,920
It's so precious. Are you sure you want to give it to me?

444
00:26:46,920 --> 00:26:50,180
I meant to give it to A'Yao's wife.

445
00:26:51,960 --> 00:26:55,760
When if we get married and then divorce? Will this still be mine?

446
00:26:55,760 --> 00:26:59,140
It's yours, forever.

447
00:26:59,140 --> 00:27:01,180
Very pretty.

448
00:27:01,180 --> 00:27:02,539
I can't bear to wear it.

449
00:27:02,540 --> 00:27:06,900
I want to leave it for my daughter or my daughter-in-law.

450
00:27:09,320 --> 00:27:13,360
Aunty, are you going to give her all these?

451
00:27:13,360 --> 00:27:16,039
I can't keep them well. Insects may eat through them.

452
00:27:16,039 --> 00:27:20,220
Xu Hongdou, you have to marry me if you accept this.

453
00:27:20,220 --> 00:27:22,539
I don't care. This present is mine.

454
00:27:22,539 --> 00:27:24,040
Ms. Xie said so, right?

455
00:27:24,040 --> 00:27:26,880
Yes, I did.

456
00:27:27,560 --> 00:27:29,740
You're really benefitting from our relationship.

457
00:27:29,740 --> 00:27:33,380
Such embroidered ornaments can't even be bought now.

458
00:27:39,700 --> 00:27:41,059
<i>[Singing Nana-chan]
Hello, everyone.</i>

459
00:27:41,060 --> 00:27:43,280
<i>I'm Singing Nana-chan.</i>

460
00:27:43,280 --> 00:27:45,640
<i>I'm back to sing for you.</i>

461
00:27:45,640 --> 00:27:48,960
<i>I haven't live streamed for over a year.</i>

462
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:52,120
<i>I planned to stop my career as a streamer.</i>

463
00:27:52,120 --> 00:27:55,339
<i>Right now, I'm working in a cafe in Yunnan.</i>

464
00:27:55,340 --> 00:27:57,179
<i>I have many good friends I made here.</i>

465
00:27:57,180 --> 00:28:00,040
<i>We all live in the same courtyard.</i>

466
00:28:00,040 --> 00:28:02,899
<i>In addition to singing, I hope to share some stories</i>

467
00:28:02,900 --> 00:28:05,259
<i>about my friends and I</i>

468
00:28:05,259 --> 00:28:08,020
<i>that I find very meaningful.</i>

469
00:28:08,020 --> 00:28:09,499
<i>Let's kick things off.</i>

470
00:28:09,500 --> 00:28:11,059
<i>As per usual, I'll sing first.</i>

471
00:28:11,060 --> 00:28:15,120
<i>Please enjoy "I'll Watch Over You".</i>

472
00:28:34,720 --> 00:28:36,780
What are you doing?

473
00:28:36,780 --> 00:28:40,500
Sister, we're having a courtyard bonding session.

474
00:28:40,500 --> 00:28:41,760
Bonding session?

475
00:28:41,760 --> 00:28:43,680
Sister Manjun, want to join us?

476
00:28:43,680 --> 00:28:45,880
Isn't that Na Na?

477
00:28:48,380 --> 00:28:50,360
Why did you send a yacht?

478
00:28:50,360 --> 00:28:52,500
Why not just give her the money upfront?

479
00:28:52,500 --> 00:28:54,900
Xia Xia, don't send such expensive gifts.

480
00:28:54,900 --> 00:28:57,880
We just need to get the ball rolling and liven up the atmosphere.

481
00:28:57,880 --> 00:29:00,020
Don't send such expensive stuff.

482
00:29:03,440 --> 00:29:08,139
Who is watching such live streams? Why are they so rich?

483
00:29:08,139 --> 00:29:12,560
She's restarting live streaming today, so the gifts are flooding in.

484
00:29:12,560 --> 00:29:14,960
Shall I start live streaming, too?

485
00:29:14,960 --> 00:29:18,399
You? Are you going to stream yourself scolding people?

486
00:29:19,580 --> 00:29:22,639
Hu Youyu! Why are you laughing? Did I scold you?

487
00:29:22,639 --> 00:29:28,140
Look. Everyone is laughing, but she only cares to snap at me.

488
00:29:28,140 --> 00:29:30,379
You're the only pushover. Of course, it's you.

489
00:29:30,379 --> 00:29:32,060
Sister Manjun.

490
00:29:32,420 --> 00:29:35,259
Wait, Sister. How can you say that?

491
00:29:35,259 --> 00:29:37,279
Teach me later. I know nothing about this.

492
00:29:37,279 --> 00:29:39,080
Okay.

493
00:29:45,260 --> 00:29:47,160
Send more gifts.

494
00:29:56,400 --> 00:30:01,660
♫ <i>Listen to the rain falling into the silent forest</i> ♫

495
00:30:03,860 --> 00:30:09,200
♫ <i>Enjoy the mountainous landscape at sunset</i> ♫

496
00:30:09,200 --> 00:30:12,980
<i>That's all for today's live stream.</i>

497
00:30:12,980 --> 00:30:17,580
♫ <i>The raindrops from the roof drip into my eyes quietly</i> ♫

498
00:30:17,580 --> 00:30:22,940
♫ <i>The world is like a quiet island</i> ♫

499
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:26,399
<i>Are you trying to use the live stream</i>

500
00:30:26,400 --> 00:30:30,420
<i>to appear as a meritorious person? </i>

501
00:30:34,320 --> 00:30:36,880
<i>My current boss shared some words with me</i>

502
00:30:36,880 --> 00:30:38,600
<i>before today's live stream.</i>

503
00:30:38,600 --> 00:30:40,900
<i>Let me read it for you.</i>

504
00:30:47,320 --> 00:30:49,480
<i>There will always be people who love you,</i>

505
00:30:49,480 --> 00:30:51,300
<i>hate you,</i>

506
00:30:51,300 --> 00:30:53,260
<i>support you,</i>

507
00:30:53,260 --> 00:30:55,260
<i>and despise you.</i>

508
00:30:55,260 --> 00:30:57,040
<i>Some hope you will do well.</i>

509
00:30:57,040 --> 00:30:59,080
<i>Some want you to die.</i>

510
00:30:59,080 --> 00:31:01,180
<i>Some wish you to be free.</i>

511
00:31:01,180 --> 00:31:04,820
<i>Some try to control you.</i>

512
00:31:04,820 --> 00:31:07,799
<i>There will be undersetandings and misunderstandings</i>

513
00:31:07,799 --> 00:31:10,080
<i>in our lives.</i>

514
00:31:10,080 --> 00:31:13,040
<i>However, everyone lives in this manner.</i>

515
00:31:13,040 --> 00:31:15,160
<i>There are no exceptions.</i>

516
00:31:16,240 --> 00:31:19,700
<i>So... think whatever you want.</i>

517
00:31:19,700 --> 00:31:22,940
<i>My dear friends, see you tomorrow.</i>

518
00:31:24,280 --> 00:31:32,020
♫ <i>I'll head to a windy place to meet you</i> ♫

519
00:31:41,400 --> 00:31:43,979
<i>That's her. A'Yao's girlfriend.</i>

520
00:31:43,979 --> 00:31:46,260
<i>From Beijing.</i>

521
00:31:54,160 --> 00:31:56,040
President Xu!

522
00:31:56,040 --> 00:31:57,800
Ye Sen!

523
00:31:57,800 --> 00:31:59,380
Chairman Xie said you're unloading ceramic tiles today.

524
00:31:59,380 --> 00:32:02,740
He's busy, so he asked me to come and help you.

525
00:32:02,740 --> 00:32:04,579
Why is he busy?

526
00:32:04,579 --> 00:32:06,659
His former colleague introduced him to an investor.

527
00:32:06,660 --> 00:32:09,080
They've gone to the village committee together.

528
00:32:09,840 --> 00:32:12,759
What investor? He never mentioned this before.

529
00:32:12,759 --> 00:32:16,020
An expert in tourist development.

530
00:32:16,020 --> 00:32:19,240
He said he was here to tour Dali and drove here himself.

531
00:32:19,240 --> 00:32:23,039
I reckon he's similar to President Liu of the bookstore, scared of grand receptions.

532
00:32:24,920 --> 00:32:27,140
Park your bike there and have some tea.

533
00:32:27,140 --> 00:32:28,340
We're almost done.

534
00:32:28,340 --> 00:32:30,300
Hold on a second.

535
00:32:32,840 --> 00:32:35,160
That was quite an old wall.

536
00:32:35,160 --> 00:32:36,899
We'll preserve it instead of demolishing it.

537
00:32:36,900 --> 00:32:38,240
It's a historical spot.

538
00:32:38,240 --> 00:32:41,920
We make renovations for the preservation of many old houses.

539
00:32:41,920 --> 00:32:44,360
Where will the bookstore be?

540
00:32:44,360 --> 00:32:47,900
An old house in the farthest part of the village.

541
00:32:47,900 --> 00:32:50,020
- This way, please.
- Sure.

542
00:32:52,400 --> 00:32:54,380
Have a seat.

543
00:33:06,240 --> 00:33:07,899
Everyone is here!

544
00:33:07,899 --> 00:33:09,399
- A'Gui, you're back!
- A'Gui!

545
00:33:09,399 --> 00:33:10,680
Hello!

546
00:33:10,680 --> 00:33:11,799
You're back!

547
00:33:11,799 --> 00:33:13,779
- Yes, I'm back.
- When did you come back?

548
00:33:13,779 --> 00:33:16,420
Just now.

549
00:33:16,420 --> 00:33:20,099
Qingdao has a lot of seafood.

550
00:33:20,100 --> 00:33:22,680
Everything was delicious!

551
00:33:27,940 --> 00:33:33,060
A'Feng, I brought you dried squid and fish.

552
00:33:34,140 --> 00:33:35,620
I won't bother you guys.

553
00:33:35,620 --> 00:33:38,280
I'll leave once I hand out the gifts.

554
00:33:39,380 --> 00:33:42,419
How was your trip? Did you have fun?

555
00:33:43,260 --> 00:33:45,200
It was so amazing!

556
00:33:45,200 --> 00:33:48,960
That darned Zeqing

557
00:33:48,960 --> 00:33:50,599
said he doesn't like living in a building.

558
00:33:50,599 --> 00:33:52,739
Our children's home was already large,

559
00:33:52,740 --> 00:33:54,539
but he keeps saying it's like a matchbox.

560
00:33:54,540 --> 00:33:57,340
Too small.

561
00:33:57,340 --> 00:33:59,719
He doesn't have many friends either,

562
00:33:59,719 --> 00:34:02,159
so it has been quite tough for him.

563
00:34:02,159 --> 00:34:03,999
He definitely wouldn't like life there.

564
00:34:03,999 --> 00:34:07,960
That's just a wild boar who can't enjoy fine grains.

565
00:34:07,960 --> 00:34:09,199
Can you get used to life there?

566
00:34:09,199 --> 00:34:10,840
Of course!

567
00:34:10,840 --> 00:34:13,240
I was so happy there!

568
00:34:13,900 --> 00:34:16,379
I'm familiar with all the markets

569
00:34:16,379 --> 00:34:20,080
and supermarkets in the neighborhood.

570
00:34:20,080 --> 00:34:24,580
Every old lady in the neighborhood knows me.

571
00:34:24,580 --> 00:34:30,339
I even know how many kids each family has, their kid's salaries and jobs,

572
00:34:30,339 --> 00:34:31,899
and who are the filial kids.

573
00:34:31,899 --> 00:34:34,440
I know everything like the back of my hand!

574
00:34:34,440 --> 00:34:37,819
It's a waste that Aunty A'Gui isn't working in espionage!

575
00:34:37,820 --> 00:34:40,180
She's just inquisitive.

576
00:34:40,180 --> 00:34:42,459
Is A'Qiang at home? I'll visit you tonight.

577
00:34:42,459 --> 00:34:45,000
Yes, he is. He's really hardworking.

578
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:50,360
He tidies up the whole house and yard, and works in the fields.

579
00:34:50,360 --> 00:34:53,060
He's even learning to cook.

580
00:34:53,060 --> 00:34:54,679
See! What did I tell you?

581
00:34:54,679 --> 00:34:57,440
You seemed so spritely when I came in here.

582
00:34:57,440 --> 00:35:00,559
Joy puts heart into a person! Right?

583
00:35:00,559 --> 00:35:01,839
All right, Aunty A'Gui!

584
00:35:01,839 --> 00:35:04,779
Excuse me, but we're working now.

585
00:35:04,779 --> 00:35:06,880
Driving me away again?

586
00:35:06,880 --> 00:35:09,079
I get it. I'm leaving.

587
00:35:09,079 --> 00:35:11,460
I need to visit Baoping. I'll leave you to your work.

588
00:35:11,460 --> 00:35:12,859
- Take care.
- Take care!

589
00:35:12,860 --> 00:35:15,259
Qingdao's seafood is so tasty!

590
00:35:15,260 --> 00:35:17,039
- Aunty, take care!
- Okay, I'm off.

591
00:35:17,039 --> 00:35:19,200
Take care.

592
00:35:20,340 --> 00:35:23,219
Here you go. Fried taro with seaweed.

593
00:35:23,219 --> 00:35:24,340
Thank you.

594
00:35:24,340 --> 00:35:25,600
Aunty Hua!

595
00:35:25,600 --> 00:35:27,499
A'Yao, we were just talking about you.

596
00:35:27,500 --> 00:35:29,279
Luckily, you didn't come at lunchtime.

597
00:35:29,279 --> 00:35:30,699
Otherwise, there wouldn't be seats for you.

598
00:35:30,700 --> 00:35:32,220
- Is your business that good?
- Yeah.

599
00:35:32,220 --> 00:35:33,240
Congratulations.

600
00:35:33,240 --> 00:35:37,280
Tons of people specially came here from the town,

601
00:35:37,280 --> 00:35:39,560
but we're decided to go on a break.

602
00:35:40,260 --> 00:35:43,119
Xiangdong's arm hurts so badly, he needs a numbing injection.

603
00:35:43,119 --> 00:35:44,879
He's suffering from varicosity in his legs as well.

604
00:35:44,879 --> 00:35:46,399
The doctor asked him to rest.

605
00:35:46,399 --> 00:35:48,659
We've discussed this with Honghong and her husband.

606
00:35:48,660 --> 00:35:52,199
They'll come back next month to help us operate the restaurant.

607
00:35:52,300 --> 00:35:55,100
- Honghong is returning with her husband?
- That's great!

608
00:35:56,440 --> 00:35:57,759
Enjoy your food.

609
00:35:57,759 --> 00:35:59,000
Call me if you need anything.

610
00:35:59,100 --> 00:35:59,499
- Okay.
- Thank you.

611
00:36:02,360 --> 00:36:04,060
